The Maybelline Fit Me Tint is a lightweight foundation that's perfect for those who prefer a natural, skin-like finish. It offers sheer to medium coverage, effectively evening out skin tone and blurring minor imperfections. The formula is non-comedogenic and breathable, making it suitable for all skin types, including sensitive and acne-prone skin. Plus, it's available in a wide range of shades, catering to various skin tones. The packaging is travel-friendly and the price point is quite affordable. On the downside, it might not be the best choice for those who prefer full coverage or have a lot of blemishes to cover. Overall, it's a great everyday foundation for a fresh, dewy look.

I've used it a couple of times and okay naman siya, but I was expecting na two gears adjustable siya as per advertised and description, pero yung dumating sakin is isa lang, so on and off lang siya, no adjustments. Mas madaling makainit yung isang side niya, so careful lang if nagpiprito kasi nauunang masunog yung side na yun. I had to turn it on and off constantly when using kasi ang init talaga. It's okay with eggs I guess kasi within minutes naluluto na siya. I've tried hotdogs pero medyo nasunog siya, and I'm not even gonna attempt to try cooking meat na lang kasi I think masusunog siya pero hilaw pa sa loob sa lakas ng init. When it comes to cooking rice naman, not very ideal, wala ngang adjustable gear so if you're not careful, masusunog yung kanin mo. I had to add water pa pala when I cooked rice kasi masyadong malakas yung init kaya medyo matigas at hilaw pa siya kahit may parts na nasunog na.  Overall, for it's price, goods siya, yun nga lang nadisappoint lang ako sa fact na isang gear lang pala kaysa sa picture at nabasa ko na dalawa daw. Could've been good if ganon kasi magagamay ko maggamit pag may adjustment na ganyan. Pero it's still great naman and sometimes niluluto ko are eggs and noodles and mostly boiling water for coffee. It serves its purpose naman for these.
